Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.89,0:00:05.31,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, did you get wet in the heavy morning rain?\N{（百合香）毛利さん　午前中\Nひどい雨でしたけど→}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.31,0:00:06.61,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,No, not at all!{濡れませんでした？\N（毛利小五郎）いえ　まったく！}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.61,0:00:08.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.11,0:00:11.24,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Anyway, these fields really are vast!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.24,0:00:14.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are all of these vineyards part of your winery, Yurika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?{（毛利　蘭）\Nこのブドウ畑は全部\N百合香さんのワイナリーで？}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.91,0:00:18.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I inherited them from my late father.{ええ　亡くなった父から\N譲り受けたんです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.75,0:00:24.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, my husband Kengo, who studied agriculture, {それで　農業を勉強していた\N夫の健吾と→}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.58,0:00:30.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, a friend of mine, and I are all{友人の水町さんの３人で力を合わせて→} co-managing the Suwayama Winery together.{諏訪山ワイナリーを\N共同経営しています。}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.59,0:00:31.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!{なるほど！}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.05,0:00:37.64,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Yurika Suwayama (28)\NWinery Co-Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.80,0:00:37.64,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{Yurika Suwayama (28)\NWinery co-manager\N---------------------------------------}I'm not too familiar with working on the field,{私は　あんまり\N畑仕事には詳しくなくて→} {Yurika Suwayama (28)\NWinery co-manager\N---------------------------------------}so I rely on them to help.{２人に頼りきりなんですけど。}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.64,0:00:40.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm really looking forward to seeing what kinds of wine you've got!{どんなワインか\N実に楽しみですな！}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.89,0:00:44.89,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't go drinking too much, old man...{ワハハハハハ...！\N（コナン）\N《飲み過ぎるなよ　おっちゃん》}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.92,0:03:00.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a truly elegant wine!{うむ　非常にエレガントな味の\Nワインですなぁ！}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.47,0:03:03.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must be quite the wine connoisseur,{（山口）\Nこのワインをエレガントと表現するとは→}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.56,0:03:06.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,recognising this wine's elegant taste! {あなた\Nなかなか鋭いですねぇ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.14,0:03:10.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right. I'm quite picky when it comes to wine.{ま　そうですねぇ\N私は　ワインにうるさいですから。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.44,0:03:14.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You just pulled that out of thin air, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.90,0:03:20.61,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Akihiro Yamaguchi (41)\NRestaurant Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.07,0:03:20.61,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm Akihiro Yamaguchi —\hI manage several restaurants in Tōkyō.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.61,0:03:26.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've fallen in love with Suwayama Wine, so I'm here to sign a contract with this winery today.{諏訪山ワインに\N惚れ込んでいまして→ 今日は　ここと\N契約を結ぶ予定なんですよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.29,0:03:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. This wine certainly isn't just one step, but two steps above all others!{なるほど\N確かに　このワインは→ 他とは　ひと味もふた味も\N違いますからなぁ！}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.38,0:03:37.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{null.AR: Thought about using "is a beauty", but I think that'd sound weird}On top of that, one of the owners, Yurika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, is quite beautiful, don't you think?{その上　オーナーの百合香さんも美人ですしね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.30,0:03:39.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Yamaguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.{ごめんなさい　山口さん。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.59,0:03:41.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?{（山口）どうしました？}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.09,0:03:45.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't find Kengo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and he has the contract.{契約書を持っている\N健吾さんの姿が　見当たらなくて。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.31,0:03:47.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It shouldn't be too long until he's found, so could you wait?{すぐに\N見つかると思いますから。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.64,0:03:49.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Again?{（山口）えっ　またですか？}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.39,0:03:52.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah... My sincerest apologies.{ええ...　申し訳ありません。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.36,0:03:58.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yurika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s husband, Kengo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\N{はぁ...\N百合香さんの夫の健吾さんは→} is scholarly and hard to please.{学者肌の気難しい人で。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.49,0:04:01.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You could almost say he's too picky when it comes to wine making.{ワイン作りに\Nこだわり過ぎているというか。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.78,0:04:03.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For example, the last time we met...{前に会った時なんて...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.99,0:04:08.95,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}Did you really think I'd agree to a contract that'd reduce the quality of Sumayama Wine?!{諏訪山ワインの質を落とす\N契約なんか→}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.20,0:04:10.71,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kengo Suwayama (33)\NYurika's husband - Agriculturist
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.95,0:04:11.50,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}Did you really think I'd agree to a contract that'd reduce the quality of Sumayama Wine?!{僕は絶対にしないぞ！}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.50,0:04:15.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, his fastidiousness is the reason the wine tastes so good, so we can't blame him.{ま　そのこだわりあっての\Nこの味なんでしょうが。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.29,0:04:19.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure he can't find fault with today's contract, but still...{しかし　今回の契約は\N決して悪い話じゃないのに...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.13,0:04:21.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel sorry for Yurika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.{百合香さんが\Nかわいそうです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.80,0:04:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.{ああ　水町さん。→}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.51,0:04:26.43,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{Tomoaki Mizumachi (34)\NWinery Co-Manager\N------------------------------------------}Did you come across Kengo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, by any chance?{健吾さんを\N見かけなかったかしら？}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.97,0:04:29.77,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Tomoaki Mizumachi (34)\NWinery Co-Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.81,0:04:29.77,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,No. I haven't seen him since we met this morning.{いや　朝　会ったきり\N見かけてないが...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.77,0:04:34.27,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Maybe he's hiding from Yamaguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?{山口さんと会いたくなくて\N隠れてるんじゃないですか？}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.02,0:04:34.27,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Shūji Takashina (28)\NWinery Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.27,0:04:37.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{null.AR: Is it okay that I added some words for context?}Maybe he really didn't agree with this contract either.{やっぱり\N納得してないのかしら...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.48,0:04:39.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, Yurika.{大丈夫だ　百合香。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.11,0:04:43.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He may be hiding, but I think Kengo's finally ready to sign the contract.{姿は消しているけど　健吾は\N契約する気になったみたいだぞ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.41,0:04:46.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, take a look at this.{ええ？ほら　これを見てくれ。→}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.03,0:04:48.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was left on a desk in the barn.{納屋の机の上に\N置いてあったんだ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.62,0:04:51.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Kengo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} {\i1}did{\i0} sign the contract!{健吾さん　契約書に\Nサインしてくれていたのね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.96,0:04:56.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a relief! Yamaguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the contract's been found!{よかったですねぇ　山口さん\N契約書が見つかりましたよ！}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.80,0:05:01.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And with that, the contract's complete.{（山口）これで契約完了です。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.47,0:05:04.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're looking forward to working with you, Yamaguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.{よろしくお願いします。山口さん。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.47,0:05:10.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{null.AR: I'm not exactly sure if this is the right translation}Yurika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, since we're partners now, feel free to consult with me about anything.{百合香さん　水町さん\Nこれからはパートナーとして→ 何でも相談して下さい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.10,0:05:10.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.{はい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.97,0:05:14.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, where did Kengo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} go?{それにしても　健吾さんは\Nどこに行ったんでしょう？}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.52,0:05:19.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go to the barn in the south field to look for him.{私　南の畑にある納屋まで\N健吾さんを捜しに行ってきますわ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.94,0:05:21.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...{代わりに水町さん。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.53,0:05:26.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,why don't you show Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and\Ncompany around the vineyards instead?{毛利さんたちにブドウ畑の\Nご案内をしておいて下さらない？}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.84,0:05:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The field to the south has Cabernet Sauvignon.{（水町）\Nあっちの南の畑には\Nカベルネ・ソーヴィニヨン。→}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.45,0:05:35.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To the north, we grow grapes for Pinot Noir.{北の畑にはピノ・ノワールという\N品種が植えてあります。→}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.12,0:05:39.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{null.AR: I might be mistaking compound words for their individual parts here}The southern vineyard is planted on red clay,\Nwhile the northern one has gravelly sand.{南は赤土の粘土質\N北は砂れき質。→}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.24,0:05:42.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The soil varies in different places in the plantation,{同じ農園内でも\N土の種類が違いますから→}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.46,0:05:45.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so we choose the types of grapes specially to match.{それに合わせて\Nブドウの品種を変えてるんです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.47,0:05:48.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You go that far...{へぇ～\Nそういうもんなんですか。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.30,0:05:50.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The misty vineyards look beautiful!{畑に霧がかかってキレイ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.72,0:05:54.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that isn't mist, but a natural pesticide.{ああ　あれは霧じゃなくて\N自然農薬です。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.81,0:06:00.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's sprayed every day from 1 to 4 PM,{毎日１時から４時まで\N噴霧されているんですが→} so it should be stopping about now.{そろそろ終わる頃かな。}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.52,0:06:03.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You cultivate roses here too?{バラの栽培も\Nされてるんですね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.15,0:06:08.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no. Those aren't ornamental,{ああ　いえ\Nこれは観賞用じゃなくて→} but a way to combat pests.{害虫対策用なんです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.95,0:06:12.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, it's not like the roses\Nthemselves can exterminate pests.{もちろん　バラが害虫を\N退治してくれる訳じゃないですよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.58,0:06:18.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But because roses are more sensitive to pests and diseases than grapes,{（水町）バラの方が　ブドウより\N害虫や病気に弱いから→} they wither before the grapes are affected.{ブドウより\N先にダメになるんです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.96,0:06:23.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if the roses wither,{バラの花が枯れてきたら→} something's about to threaten the vineyards, right?{畑に危険が迫ってるって\Nことなんですね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.05,0:06:29.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, do you plant different kinds of roses in each field?{ねぇ　畑によって\Nバラの種類も植え替えてるの？}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.05,0:06:31.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, they're the same species.{（水町）いや　同じ種類だけど？}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.26,0:06:33.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the colours are different.{でも花の色が違うよ？}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.56,0:06:36.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's not because the roses are of a different species...{ああ　それは\Nバラの種類が違うんじゃなくて...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.81,0:06:39.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Yurika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.77,0:06:44.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you find your husband?{旦那さんは\N見つかりましたか？}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.28,0:06:51.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. I couldn't find him, so I thought I'd go and check the barrel cellar in the northern field.{いいえ　姿が見えないのでこれから北の畑にある→ 樽蔵にでも\N捜しに行こうかと思って。}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.28,0:06:52.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The barrel cellar?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.49,0:06:53.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.45,0:06:57.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's where we age the wine before bottling it.{瓶に詰める前の熟成中の\Nワインが置いてある所ですわ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.79,0:07:03.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If wine's being aged there...{熟成中という事は...。}\NWill I get to drink fresh wine?{つまり！生ワインが飲めるって\Nことですか？}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.46,0:07:05.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd be glad to accompany you there!{それは\Nご同行願いたいものですな！}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.51,0:07:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Certainly! Please, Yurika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!{ぜひ　お願いします\N百合香さん！}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.97,0:07:09.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!{ちょ　ちょっと毛利さん。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.63,0:07:11.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, let's go together.{それでは\Nご一緒しましょうか。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.80,0:07:14.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you!{ありがとうございま～っす！}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.29,0:07:37.45,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's this...?!{♪♪～《これは！？》}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.09,0:07:46.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry...{残念ですが...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.30,0:07:51.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was murdered.{（百合香）う　うう...。\N他殺だな。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.64,0:07:55.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After having his hands and legs tied, his neck was tied to this stake.{手足を縛ってから\N首をこのクイに。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.47,0:07:58.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{null.AR: Missing context, so I'm trying to guess what he's actually meaning with this line}It can't be... That wasn't supposed to...{バカな　そんなはずは...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.72,0:08:00.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He shouldn't be dead...{死んでるわけがないのに...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.56,0:08:04.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! What do you mean, he can't be dead?!{おい！死んでるわけがないって\Nどういうことだ？}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.95,0:08:15.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Momoi!{（刑事）桃井刑事！}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.03,0:08:18.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim's estimated time of death has been determined.{被害者の死亡推定時刻が判明しました。→}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.54,0:08:21.50,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It happened this afternoon, between 1:30 and 2:30.{本日　午後\N１時半から２時半の間です。}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.54,0:08:22.33,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Detective Momoi (42)\NYamanashi Police Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.50,0:08:24.79,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Is that so? What were you doing at that time?{そうか　君はその時間\N何をしていた？}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.79,0:08:30.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was working alone in the southern barn from noon until then, as Yurika asked me to.{お　俺は\N百合香に言われて→ 正午から南の納屋で\N１人で作業していました。}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.84,0:08:36.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're saying there's nobody who can confirm your alibi?{という事は　君のアリバイを\N証明してくれる人は→ 誰もいないって事だな？}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.60,0:08:38.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hold on!{ちょ　ちょっと待って下さい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.64,0:08:42.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yurika just asked me to keep Kengo locked up in here.{俺は百合香に頼まれて　健吾を\Nここに閉じ込めただけなんです。→}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.31,0:08:44.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I {\i1}did{\i0} tie the guy up, but I didn't murder him!{ヤツを縛ったけど\N殺害してなんかいません！→}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.94,0:08:45.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.86,0:08:48.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never asked you to do anything like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.44,0:08:50.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Yurika...?{そんな　百合香...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.32,0:08:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yurika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, would you please tell us what you were doing at that time?{百合香さん　一応その時間の\Nアリバイを教えてくれませんか。}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.49,0:08:58.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I, Kogorō Mouri, can vouch for Yurika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s alibi!{百合香さんのアリバイは\Nこの毛利小五郎が保証します！}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.95,0:09:04.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She came to the train station to pick us up at 1:30,{今日の１時半\N彼女は私たちを→ 駅まで\N迎えに来てくれたんです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.21,0:09:08.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and we didn't arrive at the winery until around 2:30.{そしてワイナリーに\N到着したのは２時半頃。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.71,0:09:12.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after that, Yurika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was always with us.{それからは　百合香さんは\Nずっと私たちと一緒でした。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.30,0:09:13.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.{なるほど。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.97,0:09:16.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, at around 3:30,{そういえば私\N３時半頃に一度→}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.97,0:09:21.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went to the barn in the southern field to look for Kengo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.{健吾さんを捜しに南の畑にある\N納屋に向かいましたわ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.22,0:09:26.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that doesn't match up with the estimated time of death, so don't worry about that.{まあそれは　死亡時刻と関係ない\N時間ですから問題ないですよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.15,0:09:31.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, we met Yurika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} again just after 4 o' clock.{で　私たちが百合香さんに\N再会したのが　４時過ぎぐらいで→}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.57,0:09:38.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then at 4:30, we found the body in this barrel cellar in the northern field.{北の畑にある　この樽蔵で\N遺体を発見したのが→ ４時３０分です。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.07,0:09:39.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.49,0:09:45.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, can I assume that both of you haven't left the winery premises anytime after 1 o' clock?{And then, from around one o' clock until now,{なるほど　で　お２人は\N１時頃から今まで→ would I be correct to assume you two were around the winery's premises?{ワイナリー施設の中に\Nいらっしゃったという事で→ よろしいですか？}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.96,0:09:47.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.{はい　そうです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.79,0:09:49.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, I...{あの　僕...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.54,0:09:56.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today, first thing in the morning,{今日の朝早く　雨の中\N健吾さんと水町さんが→} I saw Kengo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} walking towards the barrel cellar in the rain.{樽蔵に向かって\N歩いている姿を見かけました。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.26,0:10:02.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, how many people have keys to this barrel cellar?{ちなみに　樽蔵の鍵を\N持っているのは何人いるんです？}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.47,0:10:07.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{null.AR: Moved the "boku" to the end, to make it read better in english}Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Kengo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Yurika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and myself, four people in all.{僕と　水町さんと健吾さん\Nあと百合香さんの４人だけです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.52,0:10:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim's key was inside his pocket.{被害者の鍵はポケットの中に入っていましたな。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.48,0:10:16.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the barrel cellar was locked as well.{そして　樽蔵の鍵は\N閉められていた。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.15,0:10:23.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In a nutshell, that means whoever has a key{つまり　鍵を持っていて→} but lacks an alibi at\Nthe victim's estimated time of death must be the killer, right?{なおかつ被害者の死亡時刻に\Nアリバイがない人間が→ 犯人ということですね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.12,0:10:28.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Detective, there's something I don't get.{ねぇねぇ　刑事さん　僕どうしても\Nわからないんだけど？}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.12,0:10:29.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.13,0:10:34.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would the criminal carry Kengo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Ndead body all the way to the wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.46,0:10:36.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? The body was carried?{えっ　遺体を運んだって？}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.97,0:10:38.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yup. Just look at those.{うん　だって見てよ　アレ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.72,0:10:44.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two black lines were made by the toes of his shoes rubbing against the floor, right?{その黒い２本の線って\N靴の先が床に擦れた痕だよね？}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.10,0:10:48.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed, they match with the victim's shoes.{（桃井）\N確かに　ガイシャの靴のつま先と\N一致するな。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.14,0:10:53.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If his toes were dragged, does that mean Kengo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was originally face-down?{先が擦れているって事は→ 健吾さんは　うつぶせで倒れていたって事か。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.61,0:10:57.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, those lines are almost completely straight, right?{それにその線は\Nほぼ一直線に引かれてるでしょ？}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.65,0:11:00.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That'd mean he didn't resist at all.{ん？ってことは\N抵抗しなかった。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.12,0:11:04.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which would mean he was already dead when his body was moved.{つまり　既に息を引き取っていたということですね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.04,0:11:05.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see!{あ　そっか。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.79,0:11:09.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that must be why he has those strange bruises on his neck, right?{だからこんな変なアザが\N首に残ってるんだね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.75,0:11:15.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the rope marks on his neck{ん？首の索条痕が→} extend from under his throat to the side of his neck,{喉の下から背中の付け根にかけて残っていたのは→}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.26,0:11:21.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it means the victim was strangled from behind{うつぶせの状態で\N床に倒れていた被害者の首を→} as he was lying face-down on the floor.{後ろから絞めたから。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.76,0:11:28.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. But what reason would there be for the killer{なるほど　でも何のために\N殺害したあと→} to hang the body on the wall after the murder?{犯人は壁際から\N遺体を吊ったんですかね？}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.98,0:11:32.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Why are the ropes knotted differently?{あれれ？どうして\N縄の結び方が違うんだろう？}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.90,0:11:37.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This one is just a reef knot,{こっちの結び目は\Nただの「固結び」だけど→}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.78,0:11:41.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but Kengo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s hands and feet were both tied with two half-hitches, right?{健吾さんの手足を縛っていたのは\N「ふた結び」だよね？}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.78,0:11:43.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two half-hitches?{ふた結び？}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.28,0:11:47.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} using that knot a while ago, back at the vineyards.{さっきブドウ畑で　水町さんが\N結んでいるのを見たんだけど...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.46,0:11:51.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The two half-hitches is a kind of knot that doesn't untie easily,{「ふた結び」って\N結び目が解けにくいから→}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.79,0:11:56.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so it's a special knot often used in agriculture, right?{農作業で使われる\N特殊な結び方なんだよね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.71,0:11:59.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right, the knots were tied in different ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.51,0:12:00.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.72,0:12:07.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would the killer only use a reef knot on the one rope, when it comes untied more easily?{ a reef knot tie this rope only with a reef knot{どうして犯人は\Nこっちの結び目だけ→ if it was more likely to unloosen itself?{解ける可能性のある\N「固結び」で結んだんでしょうな。}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.22,0:12:12.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the one who did it{水町さんが犯人だったら→} and he\Nwanted to make sure the knot wouldn't be undone,{絶対　解けないように\N凶器の縄の方を→}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.02,0:12:14.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he would've done a two half-hitches knot, right?{「ふた結び」に\Nするはずですよね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.31,0:12:20.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the person who tied his limbs{もしかしたら\N手足を縛った人物と→} and the one who used a rope to hang him by the neck are separate people.{首を吊るしたロープを\N縛った人物は別人なのかも。}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.95,0:12:25.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the only one in here who doesn't have an alibi.{でも　この中でアリバイがないのは水町さんだけですよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.41,0:12:29.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He's right. Everybody but Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} has an alibi...{《その通りだ　水町さん以外\N全員にアリバイがある》}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.12,0:12:31.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no, I got mud on my shoes.{やだ　泥がついてる。}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.29,0:12:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they're my favourite pumps...{お気に入りの\Nパンプスだったのに。}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.00,0:12:38.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see... Mud!{《そうか　泥！》}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.76,0:12:47.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now I see...{《なるほどな...》}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.46,0:12:52.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That person used that to fabricate an alibi!{《あの人は　これで\Nアリバイを作ったのか！》}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.30,0:13:00.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you okay, Yurika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?{大丈夫ですか　百合香さん。}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.22,0:13:06.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} must've done all this for my sake.{恐らく　水町さんは→ 私のためを思って\N行動したんですわ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.93,0:13:10.48,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Shipping 800 bottles a year is no small feat!{（健吾）\N年間８００本も出荷するなんて\N冗談じゃない！→}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.48,0:13:15.07,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We can't make that much in our vineyard.{そんな量　うちのブドウ畑だけじゃ絶対に作れないぞ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.07,0:13:19.32,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We could harvest more grapes if we stopped doing organic farming.{有機栽培をやめれば\Nブドウの収穫量は増えるわ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.32,0:13:23.78,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And if we still don't have enough, we could always buy grapes from other vineyards.{それでも足りなかったら他の農園から→ ブドウを\N買えばいいじゃない。}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.78,0:13:28.10,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If we stopped doing organic farming or mixed other grapes with ours,{有機栽培をやめたり\N別のブドウを混ぜたりしたら→}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.10,0:13:30.83,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the quality of Suwayama Wine would suffer.{諏訪山ワインの質が\N落ちるだろ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.83,0:13:33.75,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The way business is going now, we might not have a choice.{経営が苦しいんだから\N仕方がないだろ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.75,0:13:37.17,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You speak complete nonsense!{お前らとは話にならない！}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.17,0:13:42.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{null.AR: She's keeping the subject as Mizumachi-san, but I don't know how to fit both him and Kengo in the same sentence in a way that doesn't sound forced}I'm sure that, so we could sign today's contract, he tied Kengo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and...{きっと→ 今日の契約を成立させるために\N健吾さんを...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.43,0:13:45.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That would be the motive.{これで動機が揃いましたね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.18,0:13:51.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he had no alibi at the time of the crime,{犯行時刻のアリバイもないし→} I don't think there's any doubt Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the perpetrator.{水町が犯人だと見て\Nまず間違いないかと。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.20,0:14:05.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,U-Umm...{あ　あの...？}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.49,0:14:10.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Momoi, how about you wait before arresting Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?{（変声機：小五郎の声）\N桃井刑事　水町さんを逮捕するのは待ってくれませんか。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.79,0:14:12.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?{えっ！？ど　どうしてです？}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.96,0:14:15.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've just solved all the mysteries.{今　すべての謎が\N解けたんです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.88,0:14:18.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had previously come to the wrong conclusion.{私は勘違いをしていました。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.55,0:14:22.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The perpetrator wasn't Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nbut an entirely different person.{犯人は水町さんじゃない\N別の人物なのです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.80,0:14:30.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could this be the renowned detective{まさか　これがあの有名な→} who solves nearly every case without fail,{解決率　ほぼ１００％の→} {\i1}the{\i0} Sleeping Kogorō?{眠りの小五郎ですか。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.06,0:14:32.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who is the actual murderer?{毛利さん\N一体　誰が犯人です。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.98,0:14:35.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a catch to this case.{この事件には\N落とし穴がありました。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.90,0:14:37.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A catch, you say?{落とし穴ですって。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.73,0:14:42.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The estimated time when the victim was murdered was{被害者が殺害された時刻が→} between 1:30 and 2:30.{１時半から２時半の間。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.45,0:14:48.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the people who had alibis at that time{その時間に\Nアリバイがある人間は→} would inevitably be removed from the suspect list.{必然的に\N容疑者リストから外される。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.49,0:14:51.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's standard investigation protocol.{ええ　それが\N捜査の手順ですが。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.62,0:14:58.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what if the murderer found a way to kill the victim at a convenient time without even being there at that time?{ですが　犯人が\Nその場にいなくとも→ 都合のいい時間に被害者を\N殺害することができたとしたら。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.42,0:15:05.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} tied the victim up and confined him inside the barrel cellar,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.51,0:15:14.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer entered the barrel cellar,{樽蔵に監禁したあと→ 水町さんと入れ替わるようにして\N樽蔵にやってきて→} and set a plan to murder the victim into motion.{被害者に　ある細工を施して\N殺害したのです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.52,0:15:20.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Momoi, I'll need your help to better illustrate what happened.{桃井刑事\N分かりやすく説明するために→ 少々\N手伝っていただきたいのですが。}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.53,0:15:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, sure.{ああ　はい。亡くなる前の→}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.99,0:15:25.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's reenact the situation the victim was in prior to his death.{被害者の状況を\N再現してみましょう。}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.99,0:15:29.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please start by lying face-down on the floor.{まず　床に\Nうつ伏せになって下さい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.54,0:15:31.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like this?{こうですか？}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.29,0:15:36.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now try to bend backwards while pretending your hands and legs are tied.{手足を縛られていると\N想像して→ ちょっと　背を仰け反らせて\Nみてくれませんか？}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.17,0:15:41.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-This posture is really hard to maintain!{うぅ～　こ　この体勢\Nキツいですね～！}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.55,0:15:47.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The biggest mystery were the rope marks on the victim's neck.{一番の謎は→ 被害者の首にあった\N幾つもの索条痕でした。}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.01,0:15:49.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the reason was the following:{その理由が　これです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.06,0:15:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The perpetrator used a single rope to tie the victim's neck to his legs in a way that forced his body to bend backwards. {犯人は\N被害者の体をエビ反りにして→ 首と足首を\N１つの縄で結んだんですよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.94,0:16:06.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was therefore forced to keep his body bent backwards to avoid strangling himself.{そうすると　被害者は自分で\N自分の首を絞めないように→ 体を仰け反らせ続ける。}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.95,0:16:11.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the rope left serious scars on his neck as a result.{その結果　何重もの索条痕が\N首に残ったんです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.24,0:16:12.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...{そんな...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.87,0:16:21.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the knot in the rope that was hanging from the stake and the ones used to tie his hands and feet didn't match.{壁のクイにかかっていた\Nロープの結び目と→ 手足を縛っていたロープの\N結び目が違っていたのは→ こういうわけだったのです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.21,0:16:27.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! So the bruises that had been left on the\Nvictim's neck like he was strangled from behind {なるほど　後ろから絞めたような\Nアザが残っていたのは→}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.55,0:16:32.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,were due to a rope that tied his neck to his ankles, right?{被害者の足首に\N結わえられた縄が→ 首を\N引っ張っていたからなんですね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.47,0:16:34.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why go to such great lengths?{でも　どうして　こんな細工を？}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.73,0:16:38.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I told you to start with, this was done for the sake of fabricating an alibi.{最初に　お話した通り\Nアリバイ作りのためです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.98,0:16:44.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using this method, the victim wouldn't die until he had run out of strength, earning the murderer some time.{この方法なら　被害者が力尽きて\N亡くなるまでの時間が稼げる。}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.53,0:16:48.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something that awful was done just for the sake of fabricating an alibi?!{アリバイ作りのために\Nそんなヒドイことを...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.49,0:16:55.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After creating an alibi for the victim's time of death,{被害者の死亡時刻に\Nアリバイを作ったあと→} the murderer came back to this cellar{犯人は\Nまたこの樽蔵に戻ってきて→}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.20,0:17:01.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and in order to obfuscate the evidence, removed the rope that had tied the neck with the ankles{首元と足首を\N縛っていた縄を外すと→} {細工した証拠を隠すために→}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.34,0:17:05.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and disguised the corpse as having been hung from the wall.{遺体を壁際で首を吊ったように\N見せかけたんです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.51,0:17:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's only one person who could've done that.{そんなことができるのは\Nただ１人...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.30,0:17:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yurika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you were the one who murdered Kengo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!{百合香さん→ あなたが\N健吾さんを殺害した犯人だ！}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.18,0:17:18.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of nonsense are you saying?{何をバカなことを\Nおっしゃってるの？}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.60,0:17:25.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At around 3:30, you said you were going to look for the victim and slipped out of the winery, didn't you?{あなたは３時半頃\N被害者を捜しに行くと言って→ ワイナリーを\N抜け出したでしょ？}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.07,0:17:28.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went to the southern barn at that time.{私は　その時　南の納屋に行っていましたわ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.90,0:17:30.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{null.AR: I don't know how to fit "nani ka" in here}I didn't come anywhere near this barrel cellar.{この樽蔵になんか来ていません。}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.87,0:17:33.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that is a lie.{いいえ　それは嘘です。}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.28,0:17:38.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You haven't set a single foot on the southern field today!{あなたは今日　南の畑に→ 一度も足を踏み入れていない！\Nえぇ！？}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.37,0:17:45.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the southern field, Cabernet Sauvignon grapes that prefer a red clay soil are being grown.{南の畑には\N粘土質の赤土を好む→ カベルネ・ソーヴィニヨン種の\Nブドウが植えてあります。}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.63,0:17:50.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The soil in the southern field was muddy due to the morning rain,{南の畑の土は→ 午前中に雨が降ったせいでぬかるんでいました。}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.89,0:17:53.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and moist red clay easily sticks to clothes.{湿った粘土質の赤土は\N付着しやすい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.93,0:18:01.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who had been working in the southern barn, has the southern field's characteristic red clay on his shoes.{だから　南の納屋で作業していた\N水町さんの靴には→ 南の畑　特有の\N赤い土がくっついている。}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.52,0:18:07.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, there's no red clay on your\Nshoes or the bottom of your trousers.{しかし\Nあなたの靴や裾には→ 赤い土が少しもついていない。}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.65,0:18:09.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Something like that...{そ　そんなの...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.57,0:18:11.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of evidence is that?!{なんの証拠にもならないわ！}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.95,0:18:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who killed my husband was Mizumachi!{夫を殺害したのは水町よ！}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.49,0:18:16.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! You're wrong.{いいえ！違います。}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.62,0:18:20.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} confined Kengo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} here.{確かに　水町さんは\N健吾さんを　ここに監禁しました。}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.41,0:18:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, he didn't kill him!{が　殺害はしていない！}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.00,0:18:24.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't possibly be sure of something like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.79,0:18:26.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.09,0:18:31.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't set a foot in this barrel cellar after he first left.{なぜなら　水町さんは→ この樽蔵に\N戻って来てないからです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.38,0:18:33.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-How do you know that?{ど　どうして\Nわかるんですか？}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.55,0:18:38.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was killed between 1:30 and 2:30 in the afternoon.{被害者が亡くなったのは→ 午後１時半から２時半の間です。}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.56,0:18:44.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had been walking around the vineyard with us since 3:30.{水町さんは　午後３時半から→ 私たちと\Nブドウ畑を歩いていました。}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.56,0:18:51.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the only time he could've had to disguise his actions is between 1:30 and 3:30.{だから　彼が\N偽装工作をできる時間は→ １時半から３時半の間に\N限られています。}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.78,0:18:54.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, at that time...{ですが\Nちょうど　その時間→}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.95,0:19:03.08,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Right, from 1 to 4 PM, the fields around the barrel cellar in the north are sprayed with pyroligneous acid, a natural pesticide.{そう　午後１時から４時の間は→ 樽蔵のある北の畑では→自然農薬の\N木酢液が撒かれていました。}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.71,0:19:05.08,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.08,0:19:05.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.96,0:19:10.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pyroligneous acid is an acidic substance that is produced from the ashes of burnt wood.{木酢液って　木を燃やした\N灰から作る酸性の液体なんだ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.51,0:19:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a blue litmus test paper.{これ　リトマス試験紙の青。}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.64,0:19:16.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It reacts to acids by turning pink.{色がピンクに変われば酸性。}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.64,0:19:22.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It didn't change,{変化なし。} so Mizumachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s clothes weren't exposed to pyroligneous acid, right?{水町さんの服には\N酸性の木酢液はついてないよね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.18,0:19:24.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It's true. So, in other words, that means...{た　確かに\Nということは　つまり...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.90,0:19:30.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly, it means he didn't enter the\Nnorthern fields during that time span.{そう　彼は　その時間帯に→ 北の畑に\N入っていないということです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.90,0:19:35.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, Yurika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you {\i1}do{\i0} have pyroligneous acid on you!{ですが　百合香さん→ あなたの体には\N木酢液が付着している。}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.78,0:19:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's your evidence proving that?!{どこに\Nそんな証拠があるのよ！}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.83,0:19:40.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's your rose hairpin.{あなたのバラの髪飾りですよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.58,0:19:42.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hairpin?{えぇ！？\N髪飾り！？}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.62,0:19:48.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sported a beautiful silver shine at noon, but it's now darkened from oxidation.{昼間はキレイな銀色だったのに→ 今は酸化して黒ずんでいます。}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.63,0:19:53.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Silverwork is darkened when exposed to acidic liquids.{銀細工は　酸性の液体が\N降りかかると酸化して黒くなる。}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.63,0:20:01.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It got darkened by the pyroligneous acid from the southern fields{こ　これが黒ずんでいるのは→健吾さんを\N納屋に捜しに行った時に→} when I went to the barn looking for Kengo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!{南の畑で\N木酢液を浴びたからです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.39,0:20:03.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Such a thing couldn't have happened.{そんなことは\Nあり得ないんですよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.81,0:20:06.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please take a look at the roses outside.{外のバラの花を見て下さい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.81,0:20:14.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite all the roses being of the same breed, the ones in the southern field are yellow.{同じ品種のバラを\N植えてあるのに→} {南の畑に\N植えられていたバラの花は→ 黄色だった。}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.95,0:20:20.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The difference in the roses' colours stems from the substances that are sprayed through the fields, which are also different.{バラの花の色が違うのは→ 畑によって噴霧していた\N液体が違うからです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.33,0:20:24.00,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The northern field uses pyroligneous acid,{北の畑では酸性の木酢液を→}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.37,0:20:24.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,Pyroligenous Acid
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.29,0:20:29.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,Bordeaux Mixture
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.00,0:20:29.00,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,while the southern fields are sprayed with an alkaline Bordeaux mixture instead.{南の畑ではアルカリ性の\Nボルドー液を撒いていたんです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.00,0:20:36.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like the litmus test paper, the yellow roses turn red when constantly exposed to an acidic substance.{リトマス試験紙と同じように→黄色いバラは\N酸性の液体に触れ続けると→赤みを帯びるんですよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.01,0:20:46.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you were really walking around the southern field, your silver hairpin wouldn't have been affected.{あなたが　本当に\N南の畑を歩いていたならば→ 銀の髪飾りは\N変色していないはずです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.84,0:20:50.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could something like this...{なんてことなの...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.48,0:20:53.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could this become evidence?{こんな物が\N証拠になるなんて。}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.03,0:20:56.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, you're right.{ええ　そうです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.86,0:20:59.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I killed Kengo.{私が健吾を殺害しました。}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.53,0:21:00.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yurika...{百合香...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.53,0:21:04.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yurika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}... You did that just for the sake of signing a contract with a restaurant?{百合香さん　レストランと\N契約するために　こんなことを...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.54,0:21:08.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't do it just for the money... It was Kengo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fault!{お金のためだけじゃないわ\N健吾さんが悪いのよ！}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.88,0:21:14.13,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I get it, Yurika.{わかった　百合香。}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.76,0:21:19.18,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We must divorce.{離婚しよう。}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.34,0:21:25.43,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If you're willing to reduce the quality of Suwayama Wine, I can't stay here.{諏訪山ワインの\N質を落とすぐらいなら→ 僕は　ここから出て行く。\Nどうして！？}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.43,0:21:26.85,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.85,0:21:30.31,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You don't understand a thing about wine.{君は　ワインのことを少しも理解してない。}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.31,0:21:35.03,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I made a mistake when I decided to marry you!{君みたいな女と結婚したのが\N間違いだったんだ！}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.70,0:21:41.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't forgive him...{許せなかった...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.62,0:21:45.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{null.AR: I think she was played for a fool by Kengo, and that she saw no reason for him to choose between wine and her... but I could be wrong, so I'll leave it untranslated私をバカにした挙句\N私よりワインを選ぶなんて。}On top of making a fool of me, he chose wine over me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.70,0:21:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{null.AR: Please check, as I'm not sure this is the right TL}Who cares about types of grape?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.68,0:21:51.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who cares about types of wine?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.17,0:23:24.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did Dad already drink all the wine he was given as thanks?{お礼にもらったワイン\Nもう全部　飲んじゃったの？}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.09,0:23:28.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And these were vintage bottles that'd been praised by Yamaguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.{それって　山口さんがほめてた\Nビンテージものだよね？}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.88,0:23:31.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He should've let them age for a few years...{じゃあ\Nあと何年か寝かせておけば。}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.64,0:23:33.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then they'd have tasted even better, right?{もっと美味しくなったのにね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.80,0:23:36.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{null.AR: I did change the phrase around to force a pun. Feel free to undo this.}Don't whine, I won't drink any more wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.48,0:23:43.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10null.AR: Counter-pun, help!}The old man won't get any better no matter how long {\i1}he{\i0}'s aged, huh?{《おっちゃんは　いくら寝かせても熟成しないな...》}
